However, this brings up a question?  Do we have a precedent on what constitutes legitimate reason to conclude patch FFA? Does it have to be posted on scheduled downtime?  Or announced in broadcast in game?  Or is a vague hint from a CSR good enough?  Or l33t insider infoz?  I think maybe we need to get that straightened out.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nyca>Nyca</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Singing Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1554<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(4/11/03 7:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1141.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/slllyonec/EZemo/LeahHarp2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: It is 3:35 am pst, 4/11/2003</span><hr size=1> Rotational mobs *may* go FFA (read: FCFS) on any &quot;officially announced&quot; server down.  Be it posted on their (Sony's) site, or announced on the servers.  A vague &quot;rumor&quot; is not enough, nor is &quot;l337 insider info&quot;.<br>
